	   <tr><td colspan=2>As Mistress Ancarett said, Stonebrunt Mts are GREAT, i just wish they were released before my druid passed the level where they were beneficial.<br>Yes, gems such as fire emeralds and rubies and such drop there from pandas and gorillas. <br>Also, there are pelts galore, and you can do some nice quests there, the Wakizashi of the Frozen Skies, and Heretic Heads. The Wakizashi is a 6/22 1hs(druids can't use :( ) with a 81dd proc, good to sell for around 200pp in ec, and the heretic heads result in either a Kejekan headband (1 ac 3 wis 3 int 12 mana head slot all/all) or a swiftclaw sash, a 2 ac 2 agi haste belt.<br>JUST BEWARE ADDS!!!!!!!!!!!! All animals but snakes i believe and the Kerrans will attack you.<br><br>LOIO is great exp for soloing, i just kited the daylights out of stuff near the mill by the skeleton shack and the goblin valley, exp there was good even to 31 when soloing.<br><br>Netherbian lair is GREAT exp and GREAT loot for the level, just if you intend to kite, you should zone to Marus Seru or Dawnshroud to refresh sow.<br>There are guards in the tunnel as well. That should last you to 30<br><br>Marus Seru is also a good place itself to level, its like the new LOIO, just the loot is very poor there even though the exp is good.<br><br>You can always go to SK and kill gnolls and aviaks, fine steel loot is always nice.<br><br>Frontier Mts might be ok as well if you get to know the area.<br><br>There are a broad variety of places to hunt, just find one that suits your tastes.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
