	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 8th 4:00 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have found a couple of ways of raising weapon skills that work well for me. <br><br>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can find a group and offer to keep them SoWed if they will allow you to beat on their mobs.  I did this at the Sarnak fort at the Lake of Ill Omen.  I'd stay hidden between pulls and beat on the mobs with a fast, low damage weapon of choice.  I'd SoW when asked and everything worked out rather well. Naturally, you don't get experience this way, but you also aren't sitting and meding half the time.  <br><br>2.  Fear kiting is also good for raising combat skills.  I pull with either Snare or a DOT, depending on how far a run it is to my safe spot.  Fear the animal and beat on it as it walks away.  Just keep your DOT and Fear going and you should be fine.  I usually do this with dark blue mobs, but you could try it with harder mobs if you wish.  Between swinging your weapon and taking hits when the fear wears off, all your combat skills will go up.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 50th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
