	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're up for soloing, Stonebrunt Mountains might be a good place to visit. My druid just went from 30-31 there, and my ranger did 40-41, so you can see there's a good range. The zone is usually empty (1-5 players), and is &quot;owned&quot; by rangers and druids (SoW, track, camo, hide, snare, and Panic Animal all get a LOT of use. Levitate also gives you an edge). If there were more flat, open areas it would be almost ideal. The adds are the biggest problem, plus the fact that the kitties in the city won't came to your aid (but you can sell to them).<br><br>Focus on pandas for loot and for the Wakazashi of the Frozen Skies quest. And keep track up for heretic invaders, for the Swiftclaw Sash/Kejekan Tribal Headband quest. The quests take a lot of time, but they're profitable.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
