	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 3rd 11:22 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.48]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I never saw this mentioned anywhere else, so I believe I am the one who discovered it, but I think every druid needs to spend time hunting the centaur archers in South Karana, in their late twenties.<br><br>The reason may surprise you: Defense.&nbsp;&nbsp;These little guys shoot arrows at you that *pling* for a mere 10 hp apiece.  But they fully affect your AC/defense, in raising your defense skill.  It is one of the few places in higher levels that you can actually get hit enough to raise your AC significantly.  I hunted these guys for about 2 levels, and my defense went up around thirty-five points.  There's good loot, not much danger if you watch out for the higher level centaurs, the zone is great for kiting, and getting to work your defense skill, all in one package.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
