	   <tr><td colspan=2>Basically you will need to rely on looting at these levels.. once you get to around 32, you can start gathering friends or guildmates and start killing giants in RM.&nbsp;&nbsp;I was there on and off from 34 to 37(where i am now) and usually make about 50-75 plat per hour (not counting sales from loot).  <br><br>I am usually the primary healer in the group that we have (41 ranger, 42 monk, 29 enchanter, 39 druid(sometimes), and myself).<br><br>When i am the primary healer, i try to put up spells that are similar to a cleric line of spells.  usually best heal, regen, snare, root, Skin, DS, and DD (i use fury of air).  Depending on who is pulling, i also use Extinguish Fatigue as well... Also remember to keep everyone SOW'd and STR Buffed.<br><br>This is the first place that i started getting more than 5 plat splits from kills.  I wil say that you can get some decent sellable loot in High Keep too tho.<br><br><br><br>edit:<br>==============<br>Sorry forgot to add one thing here.  <br><br>At L29 you will get a self only port to Misty Thicket.  As a halfling, you will get much better prices in Rivervale.  Once you have this port, there is no reason to sell your loot anywhere except in Rivervale.  You will get the best prices if you go to the druid guild and sell.  If you have any CHA enhancing items, then that will be helpful too.  After selling, Gate back to where you are hunting.<br>==============<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon May  6 17:13:43 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
