	   <tr><td colspan=2>Halfling= most well rounded (figurativly and literally)<br><br>Wood Elf= highest pure class applicable stats (wis/cha)<br><br>Human= some say they level faster (not sure if this is true), but mainly respect.<br><br>Half Elf= Think the respect of humans x10. If you make it far as one of these kudos to you. + you get highest dex (which means less fizzles when hit) and a really good cha (for charming mobs)<br><br>I have to say that as a druid you get a cool spot in the EQ classes. With the exception of the half elves handicapped wisdom and the humans lack of inate night vision (no biggie, on former gear can make up for it, and on latter you'll spend most of life past 30 or so in wolf form anyway), no real race has enough of an advantage/disadvantage.<br><br>Pick what you'll enjoy, cause what will really matter is can you stand your character at levels 20, 30, and so on when life starts to get rough and new power takes time to earn in EQ.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
