	   <a name=101958093238224></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101958093238224><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101958093238224>RE: zone</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101958093238224#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141592><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 23rd 1:02 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.02]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Try the karanas where you have lots of animals to try out your fear kiting on. SK has elephants which drop small mamouth tusks which are decent money for you level. WK is a little low unless you want to try grizzly bears. NK has grizzly bears and various beetles which are slow moving and very safe to kite, just watch for giffs, HG's, and pesky highland lions. If you hang around the guard tower or boarder you should have little problem hunting yellow beetles and highland lions. EK has gorge hounds and gnoll reavers. Gorge hounds look like wolves but are not friendly to druids, but they are easy to fear-kite. There are a few cottage areas that have guards that will help you out if you are in trouble. One note tho: it seems the guards will not attack lions, but the farmers will.&nbsp;&nbsp;Memorizing lull animal, invis to animals, and panic animal are great for crowd control.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
