	   <tr><td colspan=2>I picked a halfling druid for many of the reasons stated above, and also because in my opinion it's one of the best starting zones in the game. You can now get to about level 15 in Misty Thicket alone. It's also adjacent to a good low level dungeon (Runnyeye) and a major city (Freeport). Rivervale has a lot of quests and great for tradeskills. I've always preferred the Antonica continent to start on versus the Faydwer continent. Again, just a matter of choice. All the above posts gave excellent advice on the stats of each race.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
