	   <a name=101915655399493></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101915655399493><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101915655399493>RE: 14 lvl spells</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101915655399493#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141592><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 18th 3:08 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>14 is the first really nice spell level for druids. First take SoW because the class really only comes into it's own for solo when you have snare, root, SoW, and a good DoT. This means the second spell is Stinging Swarm. If you have the money after this then Skin Like Rock would be the next on my list. At this point in the list it depends on where you play and if you solo or group most often. Befriend animal I prefere over cascade of hail if I am soloing since you will be encountering a lot of animals and its great having a pet. If you group a lot and can find someone else to heal then cascade of hail is probably better. Also, if you fight in areas with a lot of summoned creatures than move expulse summon to this slot.<br><br>I also like having bind and gate around this point, especially when you solo since it helps mobility and can get you out of the middle of a hostle zone quickly (as long as you aren't in the middle of fight that is). You can also make a little money by offering bind and SoW for donations. I've been offered 50pp for one bind so if you really get lucky you can make some decent cash fast, but not as fast as porting starting at 29.<br><br>Invigor is more useful at higher level situations when your group is fighting for long periods of times and they need you to &quot;zing&quot; them. Levitate can be very handy in areas near lava, and summon food and water are definitely handy on long camps.<br><br>But in the overall: once you have SoW, Stinging Swarm, and Skin Like Rock the rest can be taken in pretty much any order that makes sense to you.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
