	   <a name=101914114198347></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101914114198347><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101914114198347>RE: 14 lvl spells</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101914114198347#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73409><span id=Scholar>Mistress ancarett</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>107 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 18th 10:51 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.59]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You're lucky! Level 14 has some great spells. Here is a list of my recommendations broken down into different categories: Immediately Useful, You Will Want, Useful Later, Depends.<br><br>IMMEDIATELY USEFUL:<br>Spirit of Wolf:Your number one requested spell. Buy this before you level and carry it in a backpack so you can mem it upon hitting 14.<br><br>Stinging Swarm:A damage over time spell you'll find useful up into your low twenties. It is particularly effective against rooted opponents.<br><br>Skin Like Rock: Upgrade to your HP/AC buff. Vital unless you're always grouped with a cleric whose buffs are far superior.<br><br>YOU WILL WANT<br>See Invisible: Just what it says. Cast this BEFORE you camoflague your party mates and yourself for a run through a hostile zone. You can see everyone in your group, which is helpful.<br><br>Cascade of Hail: Area Effect cold-based damage. Useful if your party is trying to take down two or more closely positioned monsters and you don't have the extras mesmerized. Not as vital as Stinging Swarm.<br><br>Expulse Summoned: 88-94 points of direct damage versus summoned monsters (elementals and the like) for only 60 mana. I used this a lot to level up in Lavastorm zone.<br><br>USEFUL LATER:<br>Bind Affinity: Useful to bind yourself and others wherever possible. You might not need this now, but once you start porting about at 19, it is invaluable!<br><br>Levitate: Especially when running across water or in some mountainous zones where line of sight is poor, levitate is the way to go. Consumes one batwing for each cast. Batwings can be bought from Erudite merchant at the buildings on the East Commons side of the West/East Commons zone.<br><br>Invigor: Some of the melee types can be less effective when their stamina bar runs low. Give them a pick me up with Invigor (Clerics also have and Enchanters have a better line of spells, plus large races don't really need this).<br><br>DEPENDS (0n your playstyle and situation)<br>Befriend Animal: Druids can charm animals as pets to assist in fighting. I have used this spells VERY rarely. The pet will attack you when the charm wears off (random timing) so it can be a double-edged sword.<br><br>Halo of Light: Only useful for races without good night vision. If you're a human druid, this will come in handy.<br><br>Summon Drink/Summon Food: Why get these? You can forage pretty well now, I expect. But these can be useful to summon food and water for a long corpse run. I've never had to use these spells for myself (but once summoned for a groupmate).<br>&nbsp;<br>-- Ancarett, who lives at <a href="http://ancarett.com" target=_new>http://ancarett.com</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
